solutions.content:
There are three conditions we need to check : 
* All letters uppercase - `SPIDERMAN`
* All letters lowercase - `spiderman`
* Only first letter uppercase - `Spiderman`

**✔️ Logic**: 

Count the `number of capital letter` and check if 
1. all letters are uppercase / or lowercase -> `count equals word-length` or `count == 0`
2. only first letter is uppercase -> `count is 1 and 0th character uppercase`

```
class Solution {
    public boolean detectCapitalUse(String word) {
        int capitals = 0;
        for(char ch : word.toCharArray()) {
            if(Character.isUpperCase(ch))
                capitals++;
        }
        // case 1 and case 2
        if(capitals == word.length() || capitals == 0) return true;
        return capitals == 1 && Character.isUpperCase(word.charAt(0));  // case 3
    }
}
```

**✔️ Complexity Analysis**:
* TC : `O(n)`
* SC : `O(1)`

