## Explanation:

### Solution 01

- Here we’re taking 2 integer variables & 1 bool variable:
    - ***************************lowercase:*************************** keep track of the count of lowercase characters
    - ***************************uppercase:*************************** keep track of the count of uppercase characters
    - ***************************temp:*************************** true if starting letter is uppercase, else false
- If ***word*** has only one letter then return true.
- We’ll run a for loop and check 2 conditions:
    - if the current letter is uppercase check `temp == 0 || lowercase > 0` → return false
    - else the letter is lowercase & if we have more than 1 uppercase exist then → return false
- If this 2 doesn’t satisfy the condition then → return true.
- **Time complexity:** O(n).

---

## Code:

```cpp
//Solution 01:
class Solution {
public:
    bool detectCapitalUse(string word) {
        int n = word.size(), lowercase = 0, uppercase = 0;

        if(n == 1) return true;

				bool temp = 0;
        if(word[0]>= 'A' && word[0]<= 'Z') temp = 1;

        for(int i=1; i<n; i++){
            if(word[i]>= 'A' && word[i]<= 'Z'){
                uppercase++;
                if(temp == 0 || lowercase > 0) return 0;
            } 
            else{
                if(uppercase>0) return 0;
                lowercase++;
            } 
        }
        return 1;
    }
};
```

