# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
There are a just a few  conditions we need to check and the rest is based upon coding those conditions appropriately!

The conditions are:
1) If the first character is Capital, then either all the other characters also must be Capital or LowerCase. Else, we should return false;
1) If the first character is not Capital, then we should all the other characters  in LowerCase.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Inorder to implement the Above Stated Conditions, we must have several pieces of code written.

We implement in the following manner:
1) Checking whether the string is a single character long. If yes, return true, else continue.
2) Checking whether the first character is Capital or not.
3) If Capital, then in order to return true we must have either of the two conditions. That is, str[1.....n-1] must contain all LowerCase or UpperCase characters but no combinations of these.
4) If first character is not capital, then we must have all the other characters as LowerCase characters.

