This question can easily be solved by counting number of upper case letters in the word.

We can say that, the word is valid for these three conditions:
- number of upper case letters is zero
- number of upper case letter is equal to string length
- only first letter is upper case
Else we can return false

```
class Solution {
public:
    bool detectCapitalUse(string word) {
        int countUpperCase = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i < word.length(); i++) {
            if(isupper(word[i])) countUpperCase++;
        }
        if(countUpperCase == 0 ||
           countUpperCase == word.length() ||
           countUpperCase == 1 && isupper(word[0])) return true;
        else return false;
    }
};
```

This solution loops through the string only once => O(n) time complexity
Space used is constant => O(1) space complexity

