# ✨Intuition✨
Straightforward problem with considering the **first**, **second** and the **rest** of the letters.

Thanks LeetCode for a REAL simple problem for 2023!

# ✨Approach✨
Considering the wrong words is easier than considering the good ones.
So a word is incorrectly spelled if:
- The second letter is not capital and there is a capital in the rest of the word (for example, FlaG), or if
- The first and second letters are all capital and there is a non-capital letter found.

That's basically it! If you have any questions, concerns or complaints, feel free to post them in the comments below.

# ✨Code✨
```
class Solution {
public:
    bool detectCapitalUse(string word) {
        string dic = "ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ", dic1 = "abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz";
        bool flag = false, flag1 = false, ans = true;
        for (int j = 0; j < dic.size(); j++) {
            if (word[0] == dic[j]) flag = true;
            if (word[1] == dic[j]) flag1 = true;
        }
        if (!flag and flag1) ans = false;
        for (int i = 2; i < word.size(); i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < dic.size(); j++) {
                if (word[i] == dic[j] and !flag1) ans = false;
                if (word[i] == dic1[j] and flag and flag1) ans = false;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```
# ✨Complexity✨
- Time complexity: $$O(n)$$ because it is an iterative one-pass algorithm

- Space complexity: $$O(2\times26) = O(1)$$ for the two dictionary strings

