We are iterating over every letter checking it by `ord()`, which will give ACII value of the character.  
At the end if `uppers` - number of upper characters will be checked to give us a result. 
```
class Solution:
    def detectCapitalUse(self, word: str) -> bool:
        res = False
        uppers = 0
        if ord(word[0]) < 97:
            for l in word:
                if ord(l) < 97:
                    uppers += 1

        else:
            for l in word:
                if ord(l) < 97:
                    return False

        if uppers == len(word) or uppers == 1 or uppers == 0:
            return True
        return False

```

