# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
There are two possibilities, when first letter is capital and when first letter is small. There are two cases when first letter is capital i.e. word contains only capital letters and word contains only small letter except first character. There is only one case when first letter is small i.e. all small letters.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We can divide this problem as first character and remaining characters of the word. Then simple if statements to catch false conditions and return true at last.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n)$$

- Space complexity: $$O(1)$$

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    bool detectCapitalUse(string word) {
        if(word.size() == 1) return true;
        bool first = isupper(word[0]), cap = isupper(word[1]);
        switch(first) {
            case 1:
                for(int i = 1; i < word.size(); i++) {
                    if(cap and islower(word[i])) return false;
                    if(!cap and isupper(word[i])) return false;
                } break;
            case 0:
                for(char i: word)
                    if(isupper(i)) return false;
        } return true;
    }
};
```

