# Intuition
Based on keeping the count of the uppercase letters.

# Approach
Iterate through each letter of the `word.` Check if the letter is UpperCase using `Character.isUpperCase` function. Count the number of uppercase letters. Usage of uppercase is **right** in the string if:
- All letters in this word are capitals, like "USA" i.e. `count` of uppercase is equal to the `word.length()`.
- All letters in this word are not capitals, like "leetcode" i.e. `count` of uppercase is equal to $$zero$$.
- Only the first letter in this word is capital, like "Google" i.e. `count` of uppercase is equal to $$1$$ and it is the first letter of the `word`.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:  $$O(n)$$

- Space complexity: $$O(1)$$

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public boolean detectCapitalUse(String word) 
    {
        int count=0;
        for(char c:word.toCharArray())
        {
            if(Character.isUpperCase(c))
                count++;
        }
        if(count == 0)
            return true;
        else if(count==word.length())
            return true;
        else if(count == 1)
        {
            if(Character.isUpperCase(word.charAt(0)))
                return true;
            else
                return false;
        }
        return false;
    }
}
```
